field.value:
The translation of file names to class names is too simple. For example, a dash (-) in the file name will break compilation. I have been using the following with success:

public static string GetClassName(string fileName)
		{
			fileName = fileName.ToLower();
			if (fileName.EndsWith(".aspx"))
				fileName = fileName.Substring(0, fileName.Length - 5);

			string className = fileName
				.Replace('\\', '_')
				.Replace('/', '_')
                .Replace('-', '_')
				.TrimStart('_')
				.Replace('.', '_');

			return SafeClassNamer.SafeIdentifierName(className);
		}

The SafeClassNamer class is attached.

Thanks.
